          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12739630/comment/14132809",
            "id": "14132809",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=Naganarasimha",
              "name": "Naganarasimha",
              "key": "naganarasimha",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Naganarasimha G R",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Asia/Kolkata"
            },
            "body": "Apart from security , Resource isolation , preemption many things don't work in the proposed solution. I would prefer AM & its containers are coded to reuse the containers if launching of new containers are having performance problems.",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=Naganarasimha",
              "name": "Naganarasimha",
              "key": "naganarasimha",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Naganarasimha G R",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Asia/Kolkata"
            },
            "created": "2014-09-13T16:10:31.945+0000",
            "updated": "2014-09-13T16:10:31.945+0000"
          },
          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12739630/comment/14133046",
            "id": "14133046",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=vinodkv",
              "name": "vinodkv",
              "key": "vinodkv",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Vinod Kumar Vavilapalli",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Asia/Kolkata"
            },
            "body": "Today's containers in YARN are necessarily process-trees - meaning they are separate processes with their own command-lines, environment etc. If you want an 'in-process' container, given NMs are JVMs, you need native support for some sort of a first-class JVM container in YARN. This doesn't exist today, so this ticket doesn't make much sense as of now.\n\nYour use-case is valid. And as the above comment says, the solution is to launch a container and reuse it.\n\nOne other relevant work you may be interested in is YARN-896.",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=vinodkv",
              "name": "vinodkv",
              "key": "vinodkv",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Vinod Kumar Vavilapalli",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Asia/Kolkata"
            },
            "created": "2014-09-14T01:15:34.235+0000",
            "updated": "2014-09-14T01:15:34.235+0000"
          },
          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12739630/comment/14133089",
            "id": "14133089",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=bobyangbo",
              "name": "bobyangbo",
              "key": "bobyangbo",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "BoYang",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
            },
            "body": "Yes, YARN-896 is a similar scenario. Thanks for bring in that. Is there anyone currently looking at that?\n\nBy the way, can you provide more details about \"launch a container and reuse it\"? Let's say the first job comes in and launches an application master container (process). Now the second job comes in. YARN will still launch another application master container (process) for the second one. How to make the second job reuse the previous application master container?\n\nIf you mean reuse the non-application-master containers, that might be possible. But for my scenario, it needs to reuse the application master container. Is there anyway to do that?",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=bobyangbo",
              "name": "bobyangbo",
              "key": "bobyangbo",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "BoYang",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
            },
            "created": "2014-09-14T05:19:39.906+0000",
            "updated": "2014-09-14T05:19:39.906+0000"
          },
          {
            "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12739630/comment/14245508",
            "id": "14245508",
            "author": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=vinodkv",
              "name": "vinodkv",
              "key": "vinodkv",
              "avatarUrls": {
                "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
              },
              "displayName": "Vinod Kumar Vavilapalli",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "Asia/Kolkata"
            },
            "body": "bq. Yes, YARN-896 is a similar scenario. Thanks for bring in that. Is there anyone currently looking at that?\nA bulk of work related to YARN-896 is done as part of Hadoop 2.6.\n\nbq. By the way, can you provide more details about \"launch a container and reuse it\"? [...] How to make the second job reuse the previous application master container?\nbq. If you mean reuse the non-application-master containers, that might be possible. But for my scenario, it needs to reuse the application master container. Is there anyway to do that?\nYes, I meant non-AM containers first. Reusing AMs should be done outside of YARN but getting clients directly talking to the AM. Or if the 'work' being done in the AM is very little, you can try the unmanaged AM path.",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=vinodkv",
              "name": "vinodkv",
              "key": "vinodkv",
              "avatarUrls": {
